hopobject.body: I didn't go to university onmeda.es para tu salud Unfortunately, there isn't great evidence at this point that it is working, if we define working as doing more good than harm. Extraordinary monetary policy has certainly been good for risky assets and those of us who make their livings off of them, but the economy remains curiously sluggish, with an increasing gap between rich and poor and little evidence of the kind of steady growth in living standards we saw before the growth of financialization.
